nal Park Service,c[2026]  a1 online resource (1 video ((22 min., 26 sec.)) :bsound, color  atwo-dimensional moving imagebtdi2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aThis is a publication issued by the United States federal government or produced with federal funds.  aIn scope of the U.S. Government Publishing Office Cataloging and Indexing Program (C&I) and Federal Depository Library Program (FDLP).  aMusic score Peter Kater0 aFred Keakaokalani Cachola, Rae Fujimori Godden, Rebecca Delimont, Hannah Kihalani Springer, Jesse Kekoa Kahoonei ; narrator Jackie Pualani Johnson  aHundreds of years ago, ancestral Hawaiians came upon Kekaha Waiʻole - the rugged lava fields along the Kona Coast near modern day Kailua. "Spirits of Kaloko" tells the amazing story of how our ancestors transformed this land by creating loko iʻa - fishponds. Kaloko-Honokōhau National Historical Park protects and preserves the lands that sustained our ancestors. Today, this wahi pana inspires our culture to flourish and thrive.  aClosed captions and audio description in English.  aDescription based on online resource; title from title screen (NPS, viewed Apr. 29, 2026). 0aHuman ecologyzHawaiizKailua KonaxHistory. 0aFish pondszHawaiizKailua KonaxHistory. 0aKaloko-Honokohau National Historical Park (Hawaii)0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh93006114 7aEducational films.2lcgft0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/genreForms/gf2011026219 7aInternet videos.2lcgft0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/genreForms/gf20110263371 aWheeler, Chris,d1958-eproducer,edirector.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no930161741 aHutchison, Sonny,eproducer,edirector.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no930161842 aGreat Divide Pictures.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no20040647611 aUnited States.bNational Park Service,eissuing body.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n7902280940uhttps://purl.fdlp.gov/GPO/gpo255430704 